I've made myself to understand that everything I want I can make it work at the level that I am. I don't have to be richer or more connected or more influential to get these things done. Rather I position myself with my idea so these things come to me.

So what's that one idea you got this year and haven't worked on it. Felt it wasn't the right time or it wasn't worth it? 
Guess what? All you have is all you need. Recently I found something that's helped me navigate times like this.

I get ideas from anything and everything - from movies to songs to a conversation to an observation. It's very random for me and because I've trained myself over time to listen to my thoughts and process them faster than usual, I pick up ideas quickly.
Having a great idea doesn't always mean it will fly. It will need to go through a process of refinement and development. What comes out after this is something worth executing.
Ideas are not the finished product. They are just the start of the road - more like a seed which requires soil and water and time to grow.

Everyone gets ideas at one time or another in the course of living but not very many people act on their ideas which creates the difference between the ones that are action takers and the ones that are not.
